         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ [The Town Clerk read a letter from Baron Von Mueller stating the specimen of thistle sent to him by S. T. Avery, Belfast, ¶  was the true  ¶ carduus lanceolatus ¶ , and gave some information as to ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">87.02.00</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Frederick Mandeville</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found. The text given here is from a report of the meeting of the Belfast Borough Council on 9 February 1887, in <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Belfast gazette</seg>, 11 February 1887, p. 2. For a briefer report, see Minute book 9, p. 49, Borough Council records, Port Fairy, Vic.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[The Town Clerk read a letter from Baron Von Mueller stating the specimen of thistle sent to him by S. T. Avery, Belfast,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Now Port Fairy, Vic.</p>
               </note> was the true <seg style="font-style: italic; ">carduus lanceolatus</seg>, and gave some information as to the best method of destroying same.]<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The report continued:’ The specimen was the identical thistle which was placed in the hands of Mr McMeekin, who is an expert and had sworn to it being the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">carduus lanceolatus</seg>. <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The Mayor remarked that the letter was from one of the greatest botanists in the colony, and he considered the document was a very valuable one, and he was pleased to have it before the Council.' The <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Gazette</seg> went on to report a discussion of thistle cases in the local court. 'Cr Earle remarked that in future cases the better plan would be to obtain the services of Baron Von Mueller as a witness and then the offenders would have to pay the expenses'.</p>
                  <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Carduus%20lanceolatus">Carduus lanceolatus</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
